oc:kn_0bdd331a a oc:CodePattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Standard template for all agent triggering examples" ;
    oc:codeLanguage "markdown" ;
    oc:directiveContent """<example>
Context: [what led to this interaction]
user: "[exact user message]"
assistant: "[response before triggering]"
<commentary>
[WHY this agent should trigger]
</commentary>
assistant: "I'll use the [agent-name] agent to [what it will do]."
</example>""" ;
    oc:hasRationale "This is the canonical format that Claude expects for agent description examples." .

oc:kn_358ca537 a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When writing agent example blocks" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Never omit context or commentary from example blocks. Never show the agent's output directly — only show the triggering invocation." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Missing context makes examples ambiguous; showing output instead of triggering teaches Claude the wrong behavior (responding directly instead of delegating to the agent)." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_46c30e63 a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When writing the assistant response in example blocks" ;
    oc:directiveContent "The assistant triggering response must follow the pattern: 'I'll use the [agent-name] agent to [what it will do].' — never show the agent's actual output in the example." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Examples teach Claude the triggering pattern; showing output trains Claude to respond directly instead of delegating." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_acf318bc a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When determining how many examples to write for an agent" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Include 3-4 examples covering: (1) explicit request, (2) implicit request, (3) proactive trigger after relevant work, and (4) an edge case. Minimum 2, maximum 6." ;
    oc:hasRationale "This range provides sufficient variety for reliable triggering without making the description too long." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_bd66cbc0 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Standard ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When writing any agent triggering example" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Every example block must include: Context (what led to the interaction), user message (exact phrasing), assistant response before triggering, commentary explaining WHY, and assistant response showing agent invocation." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Complete examples give Claude the full pattern for when and how to trigger an agent, not just partial signals." ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_bff954b4 a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When writing multiple examples for the same agent" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Vary user message phrasing across examples — include synonyms and alternative wordings for the same intent (e.g., 'Review my code', 'Can you check this implementation?', 'Look over these changes')." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Users express the same intent in many different ways; varied phrasings ensure the agent triggers regardless of how the request is worded." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_ccf0df0c a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Procedure ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When an agent is not triggering or triggering incorrectly" ;
    oc:directiveContent "To debug agent not triggering: 1) Check examples include relevant keywords from user message, 2) Verify context matches actual usage scenarios, 3) Confirm commentary explains triggering logic, 4) Verify assistant shows Agent tool usage. To debug over-triggering: 1) Make examples more specific, 2) Add negative examples showing when NOT to trigger." ;
    oc:stepOrder 1 .

